KeenDie.name: KeenDie
KeenDie.description: Same as the 'Fall' and 'BossDeath' actions together.

Look.name: Look
Look.description:
Wait to wake up.

This causes currently sleeping monsters to wake up when they see a player.

Chase.name: Chase
Chase.description:
Standard walking code pointer.

This chases the target object, regardless of a direct line of sight.

FaceTarget.name: FaceTarget
FaceTarget.description: Turn to face the player's direction.

CPosRefire.name: CPosRefire
CPosRefire.description:
Check line of sight to stop firing.

If the target is no longer visible, halt firing and continue chasing it.

SpidRefire.name: SpidRefire
SpidRefire.description: Check line of sight to stop firing (Spiderdemon).

TroopAttack.name: TroopAttack
TroopAttack.description: Imp fireball shot or scratch if at close range.

HeadAttack.name: HeadAttack
HeadAttack.description: Cacodemon fireball shot or bite at close range.

BruisAttack.name: BruisAttack
BruisAttack.description: Baron of Hell or Hell Knight fireball shot or scratch if at close range.

SkelMissile.name: SkelMissile
SkelMissile.description: Launch a Revenant missile. Chance of launching a homing missile.

Tracer.name: Tracer
Tracer.description: A Revenant's fireball homing action. Changes the angle to point towards the target and emits a puff of smoke.

SkelFist.name: SkelFist
SkelFist.description:
Revenant punch.

This plays the sound 'skepch' if it hits it's target.

VileChase.name: VileChase
VileChase.description:
Arch-Vile walking code pointer.

Checks to see if there is a dead monster in front of the Arch-Vile and ressurects it if so.

Fire.name: Fire
Fire.description: Keep the Arch-Vile's flame at the same position as it's target.

VileTarget.name: VileTarget
VileTarget.description: Creates an Arch-Vile flame at the target object's location.

FatAttack1.name: FatAttack1
FatAttack1.description: Mancubus shot, 2 fireballs: one straight, one left.

FatAttack2.name: FatAttack2
FatAttack2.description: Mancubus shot, 2 fireballs: one straight, one right.

FatAttack3.name: FatAttack3
FatAttack3.description: Mancubus shot, 2 fireballs: one left, one right.

SkullAttack.name: SkullAttack
SkullAttack.description:
Lost soul attack.

An attack sound is REQUIRED.

Fall.name: Fall
Fall.description:
Dead body mode.

This action enabled the object's flags Obstacle, Corpse and Dropoff.

Explode.name: Explode
Explode.description: Damage objects inside the explosion radius.

BossDeath.name: BossDeath
BossDeath.description:
Magic.

Do special effects based on map number and enemy type.

BrainScream.name: BrainScream
BrainScream.description: Play sound 'bosdth' and make special explosions (states 799-801) about 320 units south of the object.

BrainSpit.name: BrainSpit
BrainSpit.description:
Fire a spawn cube.

A landing spot thing is REQUIRED.

SpawnFly.name: SpawnFly
SpawnFly.description:
Check for spawn point.

Spawns a monster if it hits a spawn-point.

ReFire.name: ReFire
ReFire.description:
Last shooting state.

If the fire button is still held, jump back to the first shooting state instead of the state with this action.

CheckReload.name: CheckReload
CheckReload.description:
Check ammo.

If there is not enough ammo for another shot, skip the reloading states and select a different weapon.

GunFlash.name: GunFlash
GunFlash.description: Display the weapon's firing flash sprite over the regular weapon sprite.

Saw.name: Saw
Saw.description:
Player Chainsaw attack.

Eager Beaver to the rescue!

FireCGun.name: FireCGun
FireCGun.description:
Player Chaingun shot.

Also checks ammo, does not go to -1 ammo, but changes the weapon instead.

Light0.name: Light0
Light0.description: Restore the lighting level after a gun flash.

Light2.name: Light2
Light2.description: Set the light flash to bright.

BFGSpray.name: BFGSpray
BFGSpray.description:
BFG blast effect.

Casts invisible BFG rays.

FastChase.name: FastChase
FastChase.description: Fast version of the standard walking code pointer.

Spawn.description: Spawns a thing at the position of this thing.

strings.E1TEXT:
Once you beat the big badasses and
clean out the moon base you're supposed
to win, aren't you? Aren't you? Where's
your fat reward and ticket home? What
the hell is this? It's not supposed to
end this way!

It stinks like rotten meat, but looks
like the lost Deimos base.  Looks like
you're stuck on The Shores of Hell.
The only way out is through.

To continue the DOOM experience, play
The Shores of Hell and its amazing
sequel, Inferno!
strings.E2TEXT:
You've done it! The hideous cyber-
demon lord that ruled the lost Deimos
moon base has been slain and you
are triumphant! But ... where are
you? You clamber to the edge of the
moon and look down to see the awful
truth.

Deimos floats above Hell itself!
You've never heard of anyone escaping
from Hell, but you'll make the bastards
sorry they ever heard of you! Quickly,
you rappel down to  the surface of
Hell.

Now, it's on to the final chapter of
DOOM! -- Inferno.
strings.E3TEXT:
The loathsome spiderdemon that
masterminded the invasion of the moon
bases and caused so much death has had
its ass kicked for all time.

A hidden doorway opens and you enter.
You've proven too tough for Hell to
contain, and now Hell at last plays
fair -- for you emerge from the door
to see the green fields of Earth!
Home at last.

You wonder what's been happening on
Earth while you were battling evil
unleashed. It's good that no Hell-
spawn could have come through that
door with you ...
strings.E4TEXT:
the spider mastermind must have sent forth
its legions of hellspawn before your
final confrontation with that terrible
beast from hell.  but you stepped forward
and brought forth eternal damnation and
suffering upon the horde as a true hero
would in the face of something so evil.

besides, someone was gonna pay for what
happened to daisy, your pet rabbit.

but now, you see spread before you more
potential pain and gibbitude as a nation
of demons run amok among our cities.

next stop, hell on earth!
strings.C1TEXT:
YOU HAVE ENTERED DEEPLY INTO THE INFESTED
STARPORT. BUT SOMETHING IS WRONG. THE
MONSTERS HAVE BROUGHT THEIR OWN REALITY
WITH THEM, AND THE STARPORT'S TECHNOLOGY
IS BEING SUBVERTED BY THEIR PRESENCE.

AHEAD, YOU SEE AN OUTPOST OF HELL, A
FORTIFIED ZONE. IF YOU CAN GET PAST IT,
YOU CAN PENETRATE INTO THE HAUNTED HEART
OF THE STARBASE AND FIND THE CONTROLLING
SWITCH WHICH HOLDS EARTH'S POPULATION
HOSTAGE.
strings.C2TEXT:
YOU HAVE WON! YOUR VICTORY HAS ENABLED
HUMANKIND TO EVACUATE EARTH AND ESCAPE
THE NIGHTMARE.  NOW YOU ARE THE ONLY
HUMAN LEFT ON THE FACE OF THE PLANET.
CANNIBAL MUTATIONS, CARNIVOROUS ALIENS,
AND EVIL SPIRITS ARE YOUR ONLY NEIGHBORS.
YOU SIT BACK AND WAIT FOR DEATH, CONTENT
THAT YOU HAVE SAVED YOUR SPECIES.

BUT THEN, EARTH CONTROL BEAMS DOWN A
MESSAGE FROM SPACE: "SENSORS HAVE LOCATED
THE SOURCE OF THE ALIEN INVASION. IF YOU
GO THERE, YOU MAY BE ABLE TO BLOCK THEIR
ENTRY.  THE ALIEN BASE IS IN THE HEART OF
YOUR OWN HOME CITY, NOT FAR FROM THE
STARPORT." SLOWLY AND PAINFULLY YOU GET
UP AND RETURN TO THE FRAY.
strings.C3TEXT:
YOU ARE AT THE CORRUPT HEART OF THE CITY,
SURROUNDED BY THE CORPSES OF YOUR ENEMIES.
YOU SEE NO WAY TO DESTROY THE CREATURES'
ENTRYWAY ON THIS SIDE, SO YOU CLENCH YOUR
TEETH AND PLUNGE THROUGH IT.

THERE MUST BE A WAY TO CLOSE IT ON THE
OTHER SIDE. WHAT DO YOU CARE IF YOU'VE
GOT TO GO THROUGH HELL TO GET TO IT?
strings.C4TEXT:
THE HORRENDOUS VISAGE OF THE BIGGEST
DEMON YOU'VE EVER SEEN CRUMBLES BEFORE
YOU, AFTER YOU PUMP YOUR ROCKETS INTO
HIS EXPOSED BRAIN. THE MONSTER SHRIVELS
UP AND DIES, ITS THRASHING LIMBS
DEVASTATING UNTOLD MILES OF HELL'S
SURFACE.

YOU'VE DONE IT. THE INVASION IS OVER.
EARTH IS SAVED. HELL IS A WRECK. YOU
WONDER WHERE BAD FOLKS WILL GO WHEN THEY
DIE, NOW. WIPING THE SWEAT FROM YOUR
FOREHEAD YOU BEGIN THE LONG TREK BACK
HOME. REBUILDING EARTH OUGHT TO BE A
LOT MORE FUN THAN RUINING IT WAS.
strings.C5TEXT:
CONGRATULATIONS, YOU'VE FOUND THE SECRET
LEVEL! LOOKS LIKE IT'S BEEN BUILT BY
HUMANS, RATHER THAN DEMONS. YOU WONDER
WHO THE INMATES OF THIS CORNER OF HELL
WILL BE.
strings.C6TEXT:
CONGRATULATIONS, YOU'VE FOUND THE
SUPER SECRET LEVEL!  YOU'D BETTER
BLAZE THROUGH THIS ONE!
strings.P1TEXT:
You gloat over the steaming carcass of the
Guardian.  With its death, you've wrested
the Accelerator from the stinking claws
of Hell.  You relax and glance around the
room.  Damn!  There was supposed to be at
least one working prototype, but you can't
see it. The demons must have taken it.

You must find the prototype, or all your
struggles will have been wasted. Keep
moving, keep fighting, keep killing.
Oh yes, keep living, too.
strings.P2TEXT:
Even the deadly Arch-Vile labyrinth could
not stop you, and you've gotten to the
prototype Accelerator which is soon
efficiently and permanently deactivated.

You're good at that kind of thing.
strings.P3TEXT:
You've bashed and battered your way into
the heart of the devil-hive.  Time for a
Search-and-Destroy mission, aimed at the
Gatekeeper, whose foul offspring is
cascading to Earth.  Yeah, he's bad. But
you know who's worse!

Grinning evilly, you check your gear, and
get ready to give the bastard a little Hell
of your own making!
strings.P4TEXT:
The Gatekeeper's evil face is splattered
all over the place.  As its tattered corpse
collapses, an inverted Gate forms and
sucks down the shards of the last
prototype Accelerator, not to mention the
few remaining demons.  You're done. Hell
has gone back to pounding bad dead folks 
instead of good live ones.  Remember to
tell your grandkids to put a rocket
launcher in your coffin. If you go to Hell
when you die, you'll need it for some
final cleaning-up ...
strings.P5TEXT:
You've found the second-hardest level we
got. Hope you have a saved game a level or
two previous.  If not, be prepared to die
aplenty. For master marines only.
strings.P6TEXT:
Betcha wondered just what WAS the hardest
level we had ready for ya?  Now you know.
No one gets out alive.
strings.T1TEXT:
You've fought your way out of the infested
experimental labs.   It seems that UAC has
once again gulped it down.  With their
high turnover, it must be hard for poor
old UAC to buy corporate health insurance
nowadays..

Ahead lies the military complex, now
swarming with diseased horrors hot to get
their teeth into you. With luck, the
complex still has some warlike ordnance
laying around.
strings.T2TEXT:
You hear the grinding of heavy machinery
ahead.  You sure hope they're not stamping
out new hellspawn, but you're ready to
ream out a whole herd if you have to.
They might be planning a blood feast, but
you feel about as mean as two thousand
maniacs packed into one mad killer.

You don't plan to go down easy.
strings.T3TEXT:
The vista opening ahead looks real damn
familiar. Smells familiar, too -- like
fried excrement. You didn't like this
place before, and you sure as hell ain't
planning to like it now. The more you
brood on it, the madder you get.
Hefting your gun, an evil grin trickles
onto your face. Time to take some names.
strings.T4TEXT:
Suddenly, all is silent, from one horizon
to the other. The agonizing echo of Hell
fades away, the nightmare sky turns to
blue, the heaps of monster corpses start 
to evaporate along with the evil stench 
that filled the air. Jeeze, maybe you've
done it. Have you really won?

Something rumbles in the distance.
A blue light begins to glow inside the
ruined skull of the demon-spitter.
strings.T5TEXT:
What now? Looks totally different. Kind
of like King Tut's condo. Well,
whatever's here can't be any worse
than usual. Can it?  Or maybe it's best
to let sleeping gods lie..
strings.T6TEXT:
Time for a vacation. You've burst the
bowels of hell and by golly you're ready
for a break. You mutter to yourself,
Maybe someone else can kick Hell's ass
next time around. Ahead lies a quiet town,
with peaceful flowing water, quaint
buildings, and presumably no Hellspawn.

As you step off the transport, you hear
the stomp of a cyberdemon's iron shoe.

BOSS.description: This thing is a major boss.

NODMGTHRUST.name: No damage thrust
NODMGTHRUST.description: This thing does not thrust the target when damaging it.

TELESTOMP.name: Teleport stomp
TELESTOMP.description: This thing can stomp another thing when teleporting.

FLOATBOB.name: Float bobbing
FLOATBOB.description: This thing uses float bobbing movement.

IMPACT.name: Activates impact lines
IMPACT.description: This projectile can activate impact (G*) linedefs.

MCROSS.name: Activates monster lines
MCROSS.description: This thing can activate monster cross linedefs.

PCROSS.name: Activates projectile lines
PCROSS.description: This thing can activate projectile cross linedefs.

CANTLEAVEFLOORPIC.name: Cannot leave floor
CANTLEAVEFLOORPIC.description: This thing stays within it's floor type.

NONSHOOTABLE.name: Solid, non-shootable
NONSHOOTABLE.description: This thing is totally non-shootable, but still considered solid.

SEEKERMISSILE.name: Seeker projectile
SEEKERMISSILE.description: This thing is a seeker projectile (for projectile reflection).

HERETICBOUNCE.name: Heretic bounce
HERETICBOUNCE.description: This projectile will only bounce off the floor once and then enter its death state. It does not bounce off walls.

HEXENBOUNCE.name: Hexen bounce
HEXENBOUNCE.description: This projectile bounces off of walls and floors indefinitely.

DOOMBOUNCE.name: Doom bounce
DOOMBOUNCE.description: Like Hexen bouncing, but the bounce turns off if its vertical velocity is too low.

TRANSLATION1.name: Color 1 (grey\red)
TRANSLATION1.description: This thing's green colors will be mapped to grey (or red if the Color 2 flag is also set).

TRANSLATION2.name: Color 2 (brown\red)
TRANSLATION2.description: This thing's green colors will be mapped to brown (or red if the Color 1 flag is also set).

FLOORHUGGER.name: Hugs floor
FLOORHUGGER.description: This projectile stays on the floor.

CEILINGHUGGER.name: Hugs ceiling
CEILINGHUGGER.description: This projectile stays on the ceiling.

NORADIUSDMG.name: Takes no radius damage
NORADIUSDMG.description: This thing does not take radius damage.

ALWAYSPUFF.name: Always puffs
ALWAYSPUFF.description: A puff from this thing always appears, even when it hit nothing.

FULLVOLDEATH.name: Full volume death
FULLVOLDEATH.description: This thing's death sound is played at full volume regardless of distance to the listener.

DONTSPLASH.name: Do not splash
DONTSPLASH.description: This thing does not make splashes.

NOSIGHTCHECK.name: No sight checking
NOSIGHTCHECK.description: This thing goes after the first acceptable target without checking sight.

DONTOVERLAP.name: Does not pass over\under
DONTOVERLAP.description: This thing does not pass over or under other things.

FULLVOLACTIVE.name: Full volume active sound
FULLVOLACTIVE.description: This thing's active sound is played at full volume.

CLERICINVUL.name: Cleric invulnerability
CLERICINVUL.description: This thing is a player who has Hexen's Cleric's invulnerability behavior.

SKYEXPLODE.name: Explodes against sky
SKYEXPLODE.description: This projectile explodes when hitting the sky.

DONTBLAST.name: Cannot be blasted
DONTBLAST.description: This thing cannot be pushed by blasting.

CANBLAST.name: Can be blasted
CANBLAST.description: This thing is not a monster but can be blasted.

NOTARGET.name: Do not target
NOTARGET.description: This thing is not targetted when it hurts something else.

DONTGIB.name: Do not gib
DONTGIB.description: This thing is a corpse that cannot be gibbed.

NOBLOCKMONST.name: Ignore monster blocking
NOBLOCKMONST.description: This thing can cross ML_BLOCKMONSTERS linedefs.

HUNTPLAYERS.name: Hunts players
HUNTPLAYERS.description: When used with TIDtoHate, this thing will hate other players too.

CANBOUNCEWATER.name: Bounces on water
CANBOUNCEWATER.description: This projectile can bounce on water.

NOWALLBOUNCESND.name: No wall bounce sound
NOWALLBOUNCESND.description: This thing does not make a noise when bouncing off a wall.

FOILINVUL.name: Ignore invulnerability
FOILINVUL.description: This thing can hurt things with the INVULNERABLE flag.

NOTELEOTHER.name: Cannot teleport by other
NOTELEOTHER.description: This monster is unaffected by "teleport other artifact".

BLOODLESSIMPACT.name: Leave no blood
BLOODLESSIMPACT.description: This projectile does not leave blood behind.

NOEXPLODEFLOOR.name: No floor explosion
NOEXPLODEFLOOR.description: This projectile disappears at the floor instead of exploding.

PUFFONACTORS.name: Puffs on actors
PUFFONACTORS.description: A puff will appear even when hit by other things.

QUICKTORETALIATE.name: Always switch target
QUICKTORETALIATE.description: This thing will always switch targets when hurt.

NOICEDEATH.name: No ice death
NOICEDEATH.description: This thing never enters an ice death state, not even the generic one.

RANDOMIZE.name: Random initial tic count
RANDOMIZE.description: This projectile has a random initial tic count.

NOSKIN.name: Cannot use skins
NOSKIN.description: This player thing cannot use skins.

FIXMAPTHINGPOS.name: Fix thing position
FIXMAPTHINGPOS.description: Fix this thing's position when spawned as a map thing.

STRIFEDAMAGE.name: Strife projectile damage
STRIFEDAMAGE.description: This Strife projectile only does up to 4x damage, not 8x.

STANDSTILL.name: Stand still unless attacked
STANDSTILL.description: This thing should not chase targets unless attacked.

NOINFIGHTING.name: No infighting
NOINFIGHTING.description: This thing does not switch target when it's hurt.

FULLDROP.name: Is dropped, full ammo
FULLDROP.description: Same as DROPPED flag, but will still give full ammo.

SCREENSEEKER.name: Screen seeker
SCREENSEEKER.description: This thing fails the IsOkayToAttack test if potential target is outside player FOV.

NOTARGETSWITCH.name: Never switch target
NOTARGETSWITCH.description: This thing never switches target until the current one is dead.

BLOODSPLATTER.name: Blood splatter
BLOODSPLATTER.description: This thing produces blood splatter when damaged.

SYNCMOVEMENT.name: Synchronize movement
SYNCMOVEMENT.description: This thing moves idiosynchratically. The server should always send its position.

NOSPEEDCHECK.name: No speed check
NOSPEEDCHECK.description: Don't kill this projectile if it does not move.

CHASEGOAL.name: Chase goal
CHASEGOAL.description: This thing walks to a goal instead of targetting it if a valid goal is set.

VISIBILITYPULSE.name: Visibility pulse
VISIBILITYPULSE.description: This thing has a pulsing effect.
